13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3314.1 of Title 70, unless there
16 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. The Board of Regents of the University of Oklahoma is hereby
18 authorized to establish within the College of Education at the
19 University of Oklahoma a pilot program to provide high-dosage
20 mathematics tutoring for the lowest performing ninth-grade students
21 resulting from the required eighth-grade mathematics assessment
22 provided for in Section 1210.508 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma
23 Statutes.
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB1287 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 B. The pilot program described in subsection A of this section
2 shall run for public high schools in districts with thirty thousand
3 (30,000) enrolled students or greater, as well as public charter
4 schools established pursuant to the Oklahoma Charter School Act.
5 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
6 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
7 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
8 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
9 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
10 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON APPROPRIATIONS
